abstract: Poland could end up leaving the European Union because of plans by the ruling nationalists that would allow judges to be fired if they question the legitimacy of the government's judicial reforms, the Supreme Court said on Tuesday.
snippet: Poland could end up leaving the European Union because of plans by the ruling nationalists that would allow judges to be fired if they question the legitimacy of the government's judicial reforms, the Supreme Court said on Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: WARSAW — Poland could end up leaving the European Union because of plans by the ruling nationalists that would allow judges to be fired if they question the legitimacy of the government's judicial reforms, the Supreme Court said on Tuesday.
headline_main: Poland Could Exit EU Over Judicial Reform Clash: Top Polish Court
headline_print_headline: Poland Could Exit EU Over Judicial Reform Clash: Top Polish Court

abstract: Venezuela's government has sparked a holiday controversy by hanging Christmas lights in major cities, decorations that many say have no place in a country suffering chronic blackouts.
snippet: Venezuela's government has sparked a holiday controversy by hanging Christmas lights in major cities, decorations that many say have no place in a country suffering chronic blackouts.
lead_paragraph: CARACAS — Venezuela's government has sparked a holiday controversy by hanging Christmas lights in major cities, decorations that many say have no place in a country suffering chronic blackouts.
headline_main: Venezuela Christmas Decorations Light Up Anger Over Blackouts
headline_print_headline: Venezuela Christmas Decorations Light Up Anger Over Blackouts

abstract: Arsenal forward Mesut Ozil should not have spoken out to denounce human rights in China, former Barcelona and Manchester City midfielder Yaya Toure said on Tuesday, fresh from a brief stint playing in the country.
snippet: Arsenal forward Mesut Ozil should not have spoken out to denounce human rights in China, former Barcelona and Manchester City midfielder Yaya Toure said on Tuesday, fresh from a brief stint playing in the country.
lead_paragraph: DOHA, Qatar — Arsenal forward Mesut Ozil should not have spoken out to denounce human rights in China, former Barcelona and Manchester City midfielder Yaya Toure said on Tuesday, fresh from a brief stint playing in the country.
headline_main: Toure Against Ozil's Public Rebuke of China's Crackdown
headline_print_headline: Toure Against Ozil's Public Rebuke of China's Crackdown

abstract: Spain's acting Prime Minister Pedro Sanchez agreed on Tuesday to meet with Catalonia's pro-independence regional head provided that the national parliament confirms him as premier - a vote in which separatists are likely to play a crucial role.
snippet: Spain's acting Prime Minister Pedro Sanchez agreed on Tuesday to meet with Catalonia's pro-independence regional head provided that the national parliament confirms him as premier - a vote in which separatists are likely to play a crucial role.
lead_paragraph: MADRID — Spain's acting Prime Minister Pedro Sanchez agreed on Tuesday to meet with Catalonia's pro-independence regional head provided that the national parliament confirms him as premier - a vote in which separatists are likely to play a crucial role.
headline_main: Spain's Sanchez Promises Dialogue on Catalonia if Wins Confirmation Vote
headline_print_headline: Spain's Sanchez Promises Dialogue on Catalonia if Wins Confirmation Vote

abstract: We need a broad national effort to recruit volunteers to educate and counsel the incarcerated.
snippet: We need a broad national effort to recruit volunteers to educate and counsel the incarcerated.
lead_paragraph: Decades after the prison population began its growth surge, criminal justice reform has finally moved into the national conversation.

abstract: Barcelona coach Ernesto Valverde said fans can protest if they wish but must remain respectful during Wednesday's La Liga clash with Real Madrid, which is set to be a highly-politicised encounter between Spain's biggest rivals.

abstract: Rudy Giuliani, the president's personal attorney, is now openly admitting that he pushed President Donald Trump to dismiss the former ambassador to Ukraine — a key factor in the Democrats' impeachment case against his boss.

abstract: A top European human rights official expressed deep concern Tuesday over the Albanian government's push for a law that critics say would undermine free expression and media freedom in the small Balkan country.
snippet: A top European human rights official expressed deep concern Tuesday over the Albanian government's push for a law that critics say would undermine free expression and media freedom in the small Balkan country.
lead_paragraph: TIRANA, Albania — A top European human rights official expressed deep concern Tuesday over the Albanian government's push for a law that critics say would undermine free expression and media freedom in the small Balkan country.
headline_main: Rights Official Expresses Concern About Albanian Media Law
headline_print_headline: Rights Official Expresses Concern About Albanian Media Law

abstract: Archaeologists in Egypt have unveiled two new artifacts from antiquity, a rare statue of one of the country’s most famous pharaohs and a diminutive ancient sphinx.
